    THIS FILE'S ROLE IN THE OVERALL POC
    ===================================
    This dashboard is the agent-facing operational view of the
    case-management scoped application. It is the FIRST of two
    dashboards in the POC; the SECOND is the Manager View
    (../dashboards/pa_dashboards_x_[scope]_manager_view.xml). The two
    dashboards target different audiences with deliberately different
    role visibility:
      - THIS Agent Workspace - visible to x_[scope]_case_agent role AND
        x_[scope]_case_manager role (so managers can monitor agents).
        Three widgets focused on the agent's own caseload (My open cases
        list, My overdue tasks list, Case count by status donut).
        Default daily-driver view.
      - Manager View - visible to x_[scope]_case_manager role ONLY. Five
        widgets focused on team-wide aggregates and throughput KPIs.
        Operational review view.

    The Agent Workspace dashboard exposes the following three widgets in
    a two-row 12-column responsive grid layout:

        Row 1 (lists row), columns 1-12:
            Widget [1] List           column=1, width=6   columns 1 to 6
                       My Open Cases
            Widget [2] List           column=7, width=6   columns 7 to 12
                       My Overdue Tasks
        Row 2 (donut row), columns 1-12:
            Widget [3] Donut/Pie      column=1, width=12  full row 1 to 12
                       Case Count by Status

    Row 1 has two LIST widgets (width=6 each, summing to 12 = full row).
    Row 2 has a single DONUT widget (width=12 = full row). All widgets
    have height=4 (standard ServiceNow widget height). Row 2 is at row=5
    because row=1 widgets occupy rows 1 through 4 (height=4).

    The deliberate visual hierarchy is:
      - TOP-LEFT (My Open Cases): the agent's most important view -
        the cases they personally own that are still in flight. Top-left
        is the natural eye-scan starting point on any LTR-language
        dashboard.
      - TOP-RIGHT (My Overdue Tasks): the agent's second-priority view -
        the tasks across all their cases that need immediate attention.
      - BOTTOM (Case Count by Status, full-width): the team-wide context
        showing how the agent's work fits into the broader case
        distribution. Donut chart with six slices (Draft, Open, In
        Progress, Pending, Resolved, Closed). Wider rendering is
        intentional - donut chart legibility benefits from horizontal
        space for labels.

    Each widget references its underlying sys_report record by NAME
    (not by hardcoded sys_id). The reports themselves live in the
    sibling ../reports/ folder:

        Widget                     | Underlying Report                              | Chart Type
        Widget 1 my_open_cases     | ../reports/x_[scope]_my_open_cases.xml         | list
        Widget 2 my_overdue_tasks  | ../reports/x_[scope]_my_overdue_tasks.xml      | list
        Widget 3 case_count_by_status | ../reports/x_[scope]_case_count_by_status.xml | pie (donut)

    Per AAP Section 0.5.2 (Cross-File Dependencies), this dashboard
    record MUST be loaded AFTER all three referenced reports and AFTER
    both the x_[scope]_case_agent and x_[scope]_case_manager role records
    so that all cross-references resolve at Update-Set apply time. The
    Update-Set engine processes records in the order they appear in the
    master XML; the Update Set aggregator at servicenow-case-management-poc/
    update-set/x_[scope]_case_management_update_set.xml is responsible for
    inserting this file's records AFTER the corresponding reports and role
    records.

    SEMANTIC SOURCE-SIDE ANCHORS (READ-ONLY, NOT BYTE-FOR-BYTE PORTED)
    =================================================================
    The Java DTOs and aggregation classes in the existing ArkCase
    case-file plugin provide the semantic shape of what this dashboard
    replaces:

      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/
        java/com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseByStatusDto.java
        Captures (status, count) pairs returned by the ArkCase
        ActiveCaseFileByQueueServiceImpl. The ServiceNow target replaces
        this with native sys_report records (group_by=status,
        aggregate=COUNT) consumed by Widget 3 of THIS dashboard.

      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/
        java/com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/state/AcmCasesState.java
        Captures the `numberOfCases` counter used by ArkCase's module-
        state-of cards. The ServiceNow target uses GlideAggregate counts
        embedded in the sys_report records consumed by Widget 3 of THIS
        dashboard (group_by=status emits one numberOfCases per status
        slice).

      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/
        java/com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFile.java
        The ArkCase entity that the x_[scope]_case table replicates.
        Specifically, the @Column-mapped fields cm_case_status and
        cm_assignee_ are the source of the `status` and `assigned_agent`
        Choice/Reference fields filtered by Widgets 1 and 3 of THIS
        dashboard (Widget 1 filters status NOT IN (Resolved, Closed) and
        assigned_agent = current user; Widget 3 groups by status).
        The ServiceNow target uses the equivalent dictionary entries
        defined in ../dictionary/.

      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-task-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/task/model/AcmTask.java
        The ArkCase entity that the x_[scope]_case_task table replicates.
        Specifically, the @Column-mapped fields dueDate, assignee, status
        are the source of the `due_date`, `assigned_to`, `status` fields
        filtered by Widget 2 of THIS dashboard (Widget 2 filters
        due_date < today AND status != Closed AND assigned_to = current
        user). The ServiceNow target uses the equivalent dictionary
        entries defined in ../dictionary/.

    None of these Java DTOs/entities is byte-for-byte ported. The
    ArkCase Pentaho/Solr-backed reporting pipeline is replaced wholesale
    with the ServiceNow Performance Analytics-style dashboards +
    sys_report records. Per AAP Section 0.3.2 ("Document management ...
    Pentaho ... are not replicated"), no Pentaho engine exists in the
    target; no Solr facet aggregator exists in the target; aggregation
    runs natively against the GlideRecord-backed x_[scope]_case and
    x_[scope]_case_task tables at dashboard-render time.

    RECORD INVENTORY (9 RECORDS IN THIS FILE)
    =========================================
    This file uses `<unload>` as the XML root because it contains
    multiple records of multiple table classes per AAP convention
    (matching the convention used by the sibling
    ../dashboards/pa_dashboards_x_[scope]_manager_view.xml). Each
    record carries `action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"` so the Update Set engine
    inserts on first import and updates on subsequent imports without
    duplicate-sys_id errors.

      Record [1]:  sys_grid_canvas_pane    Name = x_[scope]_agent_workspace_canvas
      Record [2]:  pa_dashboards           Name = x_[scope]_agent_workspace
      Record [3]:  pa_tab                  Name = x_[scope]_agent_workspace_tab_main
      Record [4]:  pa_m2m_dashboard_tabs   anonymous; carries dashboard+tab refs
      Record [5]:  pa_dashboard_widgets    Name = x_[scope]_agent_workspace_widget_my_open_cases
      Record [6]:  pa_dashboard_widgets    Name = x_[scope]_agent_workspace_widget_my_overdue_tasks
      Record [7]:  pa_dashboard_widgets    Name = x_[scope]_agent_workspace_widget_case_count_by_status
      Record [8]:  pa_dashboard_role       anonymous; attaches dashboard to case_agent
      Record [9]:  pa_dashboard_role       anonymous; attaches dashboard to case_manager

    Records [1] through [3] are independent. Record [4] (m2m membership)
    requires [2] dashboard and [3] tab to exist. Records [5] through [7]
    (widget instances) each require [2] dashboard, [3] tab, and the
    corresponding sys_report in ../reports/ to exist. Records [8] and [9]
    (role attachments) require [2] dashboard and the corresponding role
    record in ../roles/ to exist. Within this file the records are
    emitted in dependency order (canvas first, dashboard next, tab next,
    m2m next, widgets next, roles last) to maximize Update-Set apply-time
    success.

    CROSS-REFERENCE RESOLUTION
    ==========================
    Per AAP Section 0.7.2 ("No-hardcoded-sys_id constraint"), every
    cross-reference in this file resolves by record `<name>` text content
    plus a human-readable `display_value` attribute. This matches the
    convention used by the sibling manager_view dashboard, the existing
    reports (../reports/*.xml), ACLs (../acl/*.xml), dictionary entries
    (../dictionary/*.xml), and the portal record
    (../portal/sp_portal_x_[scope]_case_portal.xml). The ServiceNow
    Update-Set engine resolves the text content against the referenced
    table's `<name>` field at apply time; the deterministic MD5(name)
    sys_id values stored on each record's own `<sys_id>` field are stable
    across re-imports onto fresh PDIs.

    Cross-reference targets used by this file:
      - <sys_scope>x_[scope]</sys_scope>             -> ../app/sys_scope/x_[scope].xml
      - <sys_package source="x_[scope]">x_[scope]</> -> ../app/sys_app/x_[scope]_case_management.xml
      - <canvas_id>x_[scope]_agent_workspace_canvas</> -> record [1] in this file
      - <dashboard>x_[scope]_agent_workspace</>      -> record [2] in this file
      - <tab>x_[scope]_agent_workspace_tab_main</>   -> record [3] in this file
      - <report>x_[scope]_my_open_cases</>           -> ../reports/x_[scope]_my_open_cases.xml
      - <report>x_[scope]_my_overdue_tasks</>        -> ../reports/x_[scope]_my_overdue_tasks.xml
      - <report>x_[scope]_case_count_by_status</>    -> ../reports/x_[scope]_case_count_by_status.xml
      - <role>x_[scope]_case_agent</>                -> ../roles/sys_user_role_x_[scope]_case_agent.xml
      - <role>x_[scope]_case_manager</>              -> ../roles/sys_user_role_x_[scope]_case_manager.xml

