    that record's canonical `<name>` (or, for anonymous records [4]
    [8] and [9] that have no `<name>` field, of the canonical
    `<sys_update_name>`). This matches the convention used by the
    sibling manager_view dashboard, the sibling reports, ACLs, and other
    artifacts in this scoped application. Re-importing this file onto
    a fresh PDI resolves the same sys_id values and idempotently updates
    the same rows rather than creating duplicates.

