        ===================================================================
        The full-width donut chart on row 2. Renders the
        ../reports/x_[scope]_case_count_by_status.xml report (type=pie)
        showing the count of all cases (across the entire team, not just
        the current agent) grouped by status. The six slices correspond
        to the six values of x_[scope]_case.status: Draft, Open,
        In Progress, Pending, Resolved, Closed.

        Position math (12-column grid):
          column=1, width=12 -> occupies columns 1-12 (full row)
          row=5, height=4    -> occupies rows 5-8

        Per AAP Section 0.4.4, this is the "team-wide context" view that
        gives the agent perspective on how their work fits into the
        broader case distribution. While Widgets 1 and 2 are PERSONAL
        (filter by current user), Widget 3 is GLOBAL (no current-user
        filter). It deliberately spans the full width of the row because
        donut chart legibility benefits from horizontal space for slice
        labels and a horizontal legend.

        Why a donut chart (not a bar): per AAP Section 0.4.4, the
        deliberate diversity of chart types pairs different chart types
        to different cardinalities - donut is suitable for low-to-medium
        cardinality (6 buckets here) where the focus is PROPORTIONS.
        The agent typically wants to see "what fraction of cases are
        Open vs Closed vs In Progress" rather than absolute counts.
        Bar would be appropriate for ordered comparison (e.g., priority);
        donut is appropriate for unordered proportional comparison.

        Per Validation Gate 6, this widget MUST render with all six
        slices populated since AAP Section 0.4.1 mandates seed data
        spanning all six status values (demo cases 01-10 hit Draft,
        Open, In Progress, Pending, Resolved, Closed - one or more
        per status).

